race.comment: MISS LOLA (13) heads a strong Waller contingent. Looked good first-up over 1200m at this track, picking up late to finish third. Gets in with 1.5kgs less under today's scale and is ideally placed over an extra 100m. Hoping McDonald has pulled the wrong rein by hopping off. EX WIFE (2) has been in the money at both runs this prep in shorter races at the provincials. Won't find this much tougher and is looking for this sort of journey now. ONMALONE (6) returned his best figure over this distance two back. Big chance if he recaptures that form. A couple of first starters are well found in early markets and are sure to be up for this - BIG TIGER (3) for Gai and Adrian and RIEZ SOUVENT (9) from the Waller camp have been trialling well look nice types in the making.
